ossible .\n But does the distinction between a recession and a mid-cycle slowdown really matter anyway, given that the US is obviously suffering from one of the worst housing and financial crises in living memory - a fact that nobody (including me) can any longer deny.\n Financial markets imply a further decline of about 20 per cent in US house prices, but financial markets are sometimes wrong (as must surely be obvious by now).\n Wages are down, debt is up, inflation is rising, espenses are rising--the US consumer doesn\'t have the money to generate any real economic growth.until a long term national economic strategy is put in to place.\n James Finnegan, London, UK\nInflation in the UK is out of control so what do the BOE do?Cut rates,economic madness in the extreme.',0,NULL,0,0,3,'','2008-06-30 18:57:45',1,'2008-06-11 03:51:51',0),(405,'http://lab.arc90.com/2006/07/link_thumbnail.php','arc90 lab : tools : Link Thumbnail','arc90 lab : tools : Link Thumbnail\nThe arc90 lab is the playground of arc90 - a New York-based technology and strategic consulting firm.\n This site is licensed under a Creative Commons Attribution 2.5 License.\n So spice up those plain old text links withLink Thumbnail, the second tool from the arc90',0,NULL,0,0,1,NULL,'2008-06-30 18:57:49',1,'2008-06-11 03:51:51',0),(406,'http://www.johnbreslin.com/blog/2008/05/20/semtech-2008-nova-spivack-radar-networks-experience-from-the-cutting-edge-of-the-semantic-market/','SemTech 2008: Nova Spivack (Radar Networks) - &#8220;Experience from the Cu','John Breslin&#8217;s Blog\nSemTech 2008: Nova Spivack (Radar Networks) - ?Experience from the Cutting Edge of the Semantic Market? at Cloudlands\nNova Spivack of Radar Networks gave a keynote talk at the 2008 Semantic Technologies Conference this morning.\n He started off by giving some background to Twine.\n When Nova pitched the original idea for the underlying platform to VCs in 2003, he was told that it was a technology in search of a problem.\n The inti